  "prompt": "Which are the best indian restaurants?",
  "response": "India is renowned for its diverse and flavorful cuisine, and there are many exceptional Indian restaurants both within India and around the world. Here are some of the best and most celebrated Indian restaurants, categorized by location:\n\n---\n\n### **In India**\n1. **Delhi**\n   - **Indian Accent** (The Lodhi, New Delhi)  \n     Known for its modern Indian cuisine and innovative dishes. Consistently ranked as one of Asia\u2019s best restaurants.\n   - **Bukhara** (ITC Maurya)  \n     Famous for its North Indian kebabs and rustic, hearty dishes.\n\n2. **Mumbai**\n   - **Bombay Canteen**  \n     Offers a contemporary take on Indian street food and regional dishes.\n   - **O Pedro**  \n     Known for its Goan and Goan-Portuguese-inspired cuisine.\n\n3. **Bengaluru**\n   - **The Fatty Bao**  \n     A fusion of Asian and Indian flavors with a trendy vibe.\n   - **Karavalli** (The Gateway Hotel)  \n     Specializes in coastal South Indian cuisine.\n\n4. **Kolkata**\n   - **Oh! Calcutta**  \n     Focuses on traditional Bengali cuisine.\n   - **Arsalan**  \n     Famous for its biryani and Mughlai dishes.\n\n5. **Chennai**\n   - **Dakshin** (ITC Grand Chola)  \n     Renowned for its authentic South Indian dishes.\n   - **Southern Spice** (Taj Coromandel)  \n     Offers a luxurious take on South Indian cuisine.\n\n---\n\n### **International Indian Restaurants**\n1. **London, UK**\n   - **Dishoom**  \n     Inspired by Bombay\u2019s old Irani caf\u00e9s, known for its breakfast and comfort food.\n   - **Gymkhana**  \n     Michelin-starred, offering elevated Indian dishes in a colonial club setting.\n\n2. **New York City, USA**\n   - **Junoon**  \n     Michelin-starred, offering refined modern Indian cuisine.\n   - **Rasika** (Washington, D.C.)  \n     Known for its innovative dishes like palak chaat and butter chicken.\n\n3. **Dubai, UAE**\n   - **Tr\u00e8sind**  \n     Modern Indian fine dining with a creative twist.\n   - **Rang Mahal by Atul Kochhar**  \n     Offers a luxurious Indian dining experience.\n\n4. **Paris, France**\n   - **Le Taj**  \n     Known for its elegant North Indian dishes.\n   - **Ginger**  \n     Offers a fusion of Indian and French flavors.\n\n5. **Melbourne, Australia**\n   - **Tonka**  \n     Modern Indian cuisine with a focus on seasonal ingredients.\n   - **Monkey King**  \n     Known for its Indo-Chinese fusion dishes.\n\n---\n\n### **How to Choose the Best Indian Restaurant**\n- **Cuisine Focus**: Decide if you\u2019re craving regional cuisine (e.g., South Indian, North Indian) or a modern fusion.\n- **Ambiance**: Some restaurants offer a fine-dining experience, while others focus on street food or casual dining.\n- **Reviews and Awards**: Check platforms like TripAdvisor, Zomato, or Michelin Guide for recommendations.\n\nLet me know if you'd like recommendations for a specific location or cuisine!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
